      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 60-year-old man who is an avid gardener in the Mississippi River Valley presents with a chronic cough, night sweats, and weight loss. A chest X-ray shows diffuse reticulonodular infiltrates. He undergoes a bronchoalveolar lavage, and the fluid shows macrophages filled with intracellular, oval yeast cells. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?</span></span></span></span></p>",
