      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 65-year-old man with a history of COPD presents with a chronic cough and a solitary pulmonary nodule on chest imaging. Histopathology from a bronchoscopic biopsy of the nodule shows spherules filled with endospores. Which antifungal agent is most appropriate for the treatment of this patient&#39;s infection?</span></span></span></span></p>",
