      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 25-year-old male with acute lymphoblastic leukemia develops a fever and neutropenia during chemotherapy. He is started on empirical antifungal therapy. Subsequently, he develops painful skin lesions, and a biopsy reveals broad-based budding yeasts. Which of the following systemic antifungal therapies is most appropriate to initiate?</span></span></span></span></p>",
